Berlusconi Holding Talks Now on Bank of Italy, Ansa Says

-- B y   J e f f r e y   D o n o v a n
-- 
2011-10-20T14:01:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-20/berlusconi-holding-talks-now-on-bank-of-italy-ansa-says.html
Prime Minister  Silvio Berlusconi  is
holding talks now with key ministers on the appointment of a
successor to  Mario Draghi  as governor of the Bank of  Italy , Ansa
newswire reported, without citing anyone.  Berlusconi is meeting at his Rome headquarters with Finance
Minister  Giulio Tremonti , his party’s leader Angelino Alfano,
and other ministers to resolve the impasse over the choice of
Draghi’s successor, Ansa said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Jeffrey Donovan  at 
 jdonovan26@bloomberg.net  